  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1952 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet shows a framed graphic illustration with five levels. The background level shows a cruise ship. From the second-last level to the foreground: a group of two sailors and two women in dark swimsuits beside a palm tree; tumbling musical notes; a dancing sailor and woman in a dark swimsuit and a straw hat; information about the film. The top left corner displays the English original film title, ‘All Ashore’, advertising it as ‘American Technicolour’. The Serbo-Croatian title, ‘Veselo iskrcavanje’ (Amusing landing), is printed in the leaflet’s lower section, along with the names of the main actors: Mikey Rooney, Dick Haymes, Peggy Ryan and Ray McDonald. Producer Jonie Taps, film production company ‘Columbia Film’, director Richard Quine and distributor ‘Makedonija’ – based in Skopje – are also mentioned.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Richard Quine and released in 1952.</ab>
